revision.text:
'''Chad Gaffield''', {{Post-nominals|country=CAN|OC|FRSC}} is a Canadian historian. He is the University Research Chair Professor in Digital Scholarship at [[University of Ottawa]] and also a Fellow of the [[Royal Society of Canada]].<ref name="uottca">{{Cite web |url=https://research.uottawa.ca/people/gaffield-chad |title=Chad Gaffield |publisher=uottawa.ca |accessdate=February 7, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://arts.uottawa.ca/history/people/gaffield-chad |title=Gaffield, Chad |publisher=uottawa.ca |accessdate=February 7, 2017}}</ref>

In 2017, he was appointed an Officer of the [[Order of Canada]] by [[Governor General of Canada|Governor General]] [[David Johnston]] for "leadership in interdisciplinary and multi-institutional collaboration as a historian and administrator, and for his pioneering work in the digital humanities".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ottawacitizen.com/news/local-news/nine-ottawans-appointed-to-the-order-of-canada| title=Nine Ottawans appointed to the Order of Canada| first=Lauren| last=Malyk| date=June 30, 2017| publisher=[[Ottawa Citizen]]}}</ref>

